Massage

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

V2 is LoHa LyCORIS, so you should place it in your models/LyCORIS folder

Now your AI girls can get some good massage! :D

Works best at around 0.5 the main keyword is massage, to try to force hands you can add "male hands". Also there are several poses:

1. (on stomach, massage) - Girl is laying on stomach. I recommend to add (on back) as a negative prompt, cause it can sometimes malfunction.

2. (on back, massage) - Girl is laying on back. Like in previous I would recommend adding tag (on stomach) as negative.

3. (girl on top, massage) - Now the girl is doing the massage, surprisingly pretty consistent.

4. (foot massage, massage) - Girl is getting a foot massage as tags implie. Very hard to get good results, but it is there. This is not feet-oriented lora, so you can get ready for common feet fingers problems. Accommodate it with such tags as: toe, feet, sole, toe, etc, so it can focus on generating feet...

You can also experiment with several interesting tags, such as: ass grab, grabbing another's ass, thigh grab, nipple tweak, breast grab, groping

Also there are lotion and towel tags, if you want the real massage experience.

Can generate boys doing massage to each other, it can happen from time to time even if you don't intent tho. Tag hetero can exclude this situation if it pops up too much. I didn't test this scenario much enough, so it's up to you.

Dataset was scraped from gelbooru, tagged with the main word massage and with one pose tag (on stomach, on back, laying on body, foot massage). Dataset contained ~300 images. There was only about 20 images about foot massage.

Astaroth (Sin: Nanatsu no Taizai)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Astaroth, Sin of Melancholy from the Seven Mortal Sins anime (Sin: Nanatsu no Taizai).

LoCon trained on NAI. The dataset does contain some mild NSFW images, so it might tend towards these if no outfit is specified. Works well with weights from 0.6~1. Higher weights might tend to veer closer to the anime's style.

I tried to isolate the following concepts so that they may be used either together or independently:

  • "astaroth" - For the character. Keywords "red eyes, tail, twintails" may help. Use as a negative prompt if attempting to use the other concepts on different characters.

  • "astarothdress" - For the main outfit. Keyword "striped thighhighs" may help for the stockings. This is somewhat overfit into the model, so use as negative prompt if attempting to change or remove the outfit.

  • "astarothguitar" - For the guitar. Keywords "playing instrument, electric guitar" may help. Kind of a hit or miss for this one, but increasing the strength also seems to help.

90s VHS TV Show Style - LoCon

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

It is one of my first models that I trained thanks to this guide:

[Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

There are LoRas and Checkpoints that reference the VHS style, and after this inspiration, I came up with the idea of being able to create a LoCon of a VHS stylized taking references to interviews, television programs, movies and commercials from the late 80s and mid 90s to create an effect not so destroyed or glitched by the quality of the VHS of that time. It was intended for portraits more than for other purposes, for landscapes and others, I am not 100% sure that it works well.

It was trained by approximately 140 portrait-type photos extracted from video fragments and other image sources.

In the training I used this checkpoint with SD 1.5 as a base, so I also recommend that you use this checkpoint in conjunction with the LoCon to obtain the most faithful result to the one I had.

(Surely there will be better combinations, better options, but that I have not tested or documented.)

How to install LoCon:

  • How to use models · civitai/civitai Wiki (github.com)

How to use it:

Prompts: 90VHS, vhs still from tv, + whatever-you-want

I also recommend using epiNoiseoffset_v1.

Negative Prompts: rz-neg-foranalogportrait, cartoon, 3d, ((disfigured)), ((bad art)), ((deformed)), ((poorly drawn)), ((extra limbs)), ((close up)), ((b&w)), weird colors, blurry

You can experiment with negative prompts, but for me ‘rz-neg-foranalogportrait’ give very good results.

I recommend these parameters:

  • LoCon Strength: 1.0

  • Size: 512 x 512 - Truly I have not tried with other resolutions, I think the most stable is this measure.

  • Sampling Steps: between 20 and 40 is the most stable.

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras works very well for portraits.

Using this LoCon in img2img interesting results are achieved maintaining 512x512, and with these settings:

Same settings as txt2img but with these differences:

  • CFG Scale: 26 ~

  • Denoising strength: 0,5 - sometimes 0,8

I invite you to experiment with checkpoints, mix them with other Loras and share them!

Don’t forget to put the prompts you used, thank you!

Токены: 90VHS
